oc:kn_159813ef a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When choosing a tool for any PDF operation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use pdfplumber for text and table extraction, pypdf for merge/split/rotate/encrypt operations, reportlab for PDF creation, and CLI tools (qpdf, pdftotext) for quick command-line tasks." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Each library has distinct strengths; choosing the right one avoids unnecessary complexity and ensures reliable results." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_4c4cb0c6 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before any PDF processing operation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always verify the PDF file exists and is readable before attempting operations. Check that required Python libraries (pypdf, pdfplumber, reportlab) are installed." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Prevents runtime errors from missing files or dependencies." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_4d154db6 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SecurityImplication ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When handling encrypted or password-protected PDFs" ;
    oc:directiveContent "When encrypting PDFs, use both user_password and owner_password parameters. When decrypting, ensure the decrypted file is stored securely and deleted after use." ;
    oc:hasRationale "PDF encryption controls document access; improper handling can expose sensitive data." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_54b40fe9 a oc:Idempotency,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When running PDF operations multiple times" ;
    oc:directiveContent "PDF merge and split operations are idempotent — re-running produces identical output. PDF creation is additive and will overwrite existing files with the same name." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Knowing idempotency characteristics helps design reliable automation pipelines without duplicate page risks." ;
    oc:severityLevel "LOW" .

oc:kn_5b80049c a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When text extraction returns empty or poor results" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For scanned PDFs, convert pages to images first using pdf2image, then apply OCR with pytesseract. Direct text extraction will return empty or garbled results on scanned documents." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Scanned PDFs contain images of text, not actual text characters, so OCR is required to make them machine-readable." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_927f7b05 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When text extraction returns empty or errors" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If pypdf fails to extract text from a PDF, fall back to pdfplumber or pdftotext CLI. If all text extraction fails, the PDF is likely scanned and requires OCR." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Different parsers handle PDF encodings and structures differently; a fallback chain maximizes extraction success." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_d883db5c a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When extracting tables from PDFs" ;
    oc:directiveContent "pdfplumber's extract_tables() returns a list of lists; always check if table results are non-empty before processing. Tables with no clear grid lines may not be detected." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Empty or malformed table results can cause downstream errors if not handled gracefully." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

